The pudendal nerve has three major branches:

The inferior rectal nerve crosses the ischioanal fossa to innervate the external anal sphincter and portions of the levator ani and the skin of the anal triangle. 
The perineal nerve enters the superficial perineal pouch to innervate its skeletal muscle, the skin of the urogenital triangle and ends as the cutaneous posterior scrotal / labial nerves. 
The third branch traverses the deep perineal pouch to end as the dorsal nerve of the penis / clitoris.
